\f3\b0\fs30 \cf20 \cb3 Namespaces and cgroups are the building blocks for containers and modern applications. Having an understanding of how they work is important as we refactor applications to more modern architectures.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl540\sa450\partightenfactor0
\cf27 Namespaces provide isolation of system resources, and cgroups allow for fine\uc0\u8209 grained control and enforcement of limits for those resources.\cf20 \
Containers are not the only way that you can use namespaces and cgroups. Namespaces and cgroup interfaces are built into the Linux kernel, which means that other applications can use them to provide separation and resource constraints.\
\
